  "texts": [
    "Specifically, this involves embedding the user's video clip input into highdimensional features using the recognition network and then comparing these features with the high-dimensional features corresponding to the target meaning within the isolated Auslan recognition model.",
    "This comparison determines whether the user's Auslan is correct (i.e., successfully conveys the intended meaning).",
    "This feedback mechanism creates a loop of Auslan learning, error correction, and further learning, allowing users to learn Auslan in a self-supervised manner.As shown in Fig. 3, when users enter the self-teaching module, they can either choose a specific Auslan gloss they wish to learn or be provided one randomly, which can also serve as a test.",
    "Once ready, the user can activate the camera to input their recorded Auslan, and the Auslan recognition system will operate as usual.",
    "The result of the Auslan recognition is then used to compare with the target word being learned, informing the user whether the Auslan performed is correct.Regardless of correctness, users can view a side-by-side playback of their own Auslan video and the demonstration video, further learning the details of the specific gloss."
